                        "name": "bsagols",
                        "displayName": "Benoit Sagols",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "hi, do we know in which release the patch will be included?\r\nIs the patch safe for production environment?\r\nthx - benoit",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bsagols",
                        "name": "bsagols",
                        "displayName": "Benoit Sagols",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-18T04:19:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-18T04:19:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40806",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bsagols",
                        "name": "bsagols",
                        "displayName": "Benoit Sagols",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi\r\nI'm using the patch in production, so far so good.\r\nI had to make a little change in the code although. Instead of defaulting _translatable to false in the __contruct method, I've set it to true and now everything works fine. I don't quite undestancd what _translatable is for...\r\n\r\nAs in Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Module patch, this is set to false in the constructor and never again manipulated afterwards... On the contrary in Zend_Controller_Router_Route, the similar variable _translatable is initialized in the contructor, looking for segments to translate in the url (looking for \"@\" sign...).\r\n\r\nHope this helps.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bsagols",
                        "name": "bsagols",
                        "displayName": "Benoit Sagols",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-31T07:43:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-31T07:43:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40954",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rs",
                        "name": "rs",
                        "displayName": "Robert",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "hi,\r\n\r\nthis issue exists nearly a year, an nobody seems really to care.\r\n\r\ni don't get it, actually this is a basic functionality and should be handled on major priority. \r\n\r\nI also posted a, from my perspective, major issue affecting the basic JSON serialization.  (http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/browse\/ZF-9416) This was fixed after nearly 3 month. This is a completely unacceptable timeframe for every kind of project.\r\n\r\nI don't know if you guys are payed by zend or if you doing it for fun in your freetime, but by next project will not base on the ZF.\r\n\r\nbr\r\nrobert  ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
